<item>
            <title>[LU-10034] LDISKFS Quota scalability improvement</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10034</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently Lustre enabled user/group accounting in default, in our testing, we found&lt;br/&gt;
that with these extra object accounting, there is big overhead especially for metadata&lt;br/&gt;
intensive workload, there will be more overhead with project quota enabled.(Numbers&lt;br/&gt;
will be attached later)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally, we could reach similar performance number with/without quota.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are some Kernel and Ext4 patches merged by Linux upstream which could&lt;br/&gt;
significantly improve the quota performance, it will be good to have them in Lustre&lt;br/&gt;
RHEL7.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
